 yellow daisy-like flowers in late summer, arranged in a capitulum with 15-30 florets, each with 5 yellow, sometimes pink or white, ray florets and 15-30 disc florets. The capitulum is 2-4 cm in diameter, and is surrounded by a bract that is leaf-like and hairy. The plant has a fibrous root system, and is commonly found in dry, sandy soils and waste places in Europe and Western Asia."}